{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015vJVXR7mK28zVuufnzafXv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017NiCs5iezJReKGdHUhF6y1","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# MongoDB Replica Set Change Plan\n\n## Current State (as inspected on 2026-06-14)\n\n### Replica set topology\n- **Name:** `mongodb-replica`\n- **Members:** 3 (all data-bearing, no arbiters, no hidden members)\n  | ID | Host | Priority | Votes | Arbiter |\n  |----|------|----------|-------|---------|\n  | 0 | `mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | No |\n  | 1 | `mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | No |\n  | 2 | `mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | No |\n- **Protocol version:** 1 (Raft-based elections)\n- **Default write concern:** `{ w: 1, wtimeout: 0 }` (replica-set default)\n\n### Applied non-default configuration (mongod-config ConfigMap)\n| Setting | Current value | MongoDB default |\n|---------|---------------|-----------------|\n| `systemLog.verbosity` | `1` | `0` |\n| `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs` | `200` ms | `100` ms |\n| `storage.wiredTiger.engineConfig.journalCompressor` | `zlib` | `snappy` |\n| `security.authorization` | `enabled` | `disabled` |\n| `security.keyFile` | `/etc/mongo-keyfile/keyfile` | none |\n| `net.bindIpAll` | `true` | `false` |\n\n### Users and roles\n| User | DB | Roles |\n|------|----|-------|\n| `admin-user` | `admin` | `userAdminAnyDatabase`, `clusterAdmin`, `readWriteAnyDatabase` |\n\nAuthentication mechanisms active on all three nodes: **SCRAM-SHA-1** and **SCRAM-SHA-256**.\n\n---\n\n## Gap Analysis — Changes Required to Reach Target Hardened Baseline\n\nThe following gaps exist between the current state and the target hardened baseline.\n\n### GAP-1: Default write concern is `w:1` (data-loss risk on primary failure)\n\n**Current:** `getLastErrorDefaults: { w: 1, wtimeout: 0 }`  \n**Target:** `{ w: \"majority\", wtimeout: 5000 }`  \nA majority write concern ensures at least two of three members have acknowledged a write before it is considered durable. `w:1` risks losing acknowledged writes if the primary fails before replication completes.\n\n### GAP-2: SCRAM-SHA-1 is enabled alongside SCRAM-SHA-256\n\n**Current:** Both `SCRAM-SHA-1` and `SCRAM-SHA-256` are negotiated (confirmed in `system.users`).  \n**Target:** Disable `SCRAM-SHA-1`; allow only `SCRAM-SHA-256`.  \nSCRAM-SHA-1 is weaker and should be removed from the allowed mechanism list to meet current hardening standards.\n\n### GAP-3: `admin-user` holds excessive combined privileges\n\n**Current:** Single user with `userAdminAnyDatabase + clusterAdmin + readWriteAnyDatabase`.  \n**Target:** Dedicated roles assigned to separate accounts:\n- A **cluster admin** account with only `clusterAdmin` + `clusterMonitor`.\n- A **user admin** account with only `userAdminAnyDatabase`.\n- An **application** account with the minimum database-scoped `readWrite` it actually needs.  \n\nCombining all three in one credential violates least-privilege and means a single credential leak grants full cluster control.\n\n### GAP-4: No dedicated monitoring user (read-only access)\n\n**Current:** No monitoring-specific user exists.  \n**Target:** A `monitor-user` with the `clusterMonitor` role in `admin` to allow Prometheus / ops tooling to scrape metrics without cluster-admin rights.\n\n### GAP-5: TLS not configured for client and intra-cluster traffic\n\n**Current:** No `net.tls` block in `mongod.conf`; all connections are plaintext.  \n**Target:** TLS enabled with `net.tls.mode: requireTLS`, server certificate, and CA certificate, for both client connections and internal replica-set member communication.  \nSteps needed:\n1. Generate a CA and per-node TLS certificates (PEM files combining cert + key) and mount them as a Kubernetes Secret.\n2. Add `net.tls` block to `mongod.conf`:\n   ```yaml\n   net:\n     tls:\n       mode: requireTLS\n       certificateKeyFile: /etc/mongo-tls/server.pem\n       CAFile: /etc/mongo-tls/ca.pem\n   ```\n3. Update the `mongo-keyfile`-based internal auth to a combined keyFile + TLS setup (or migrate to x.509 internal auth).\n4. Update liveness/readiness probes and any client connection strings to use `tls=true`.\n\n### GAP-6: `net.bindIpAll: true` is overly permissive\n\n**Current:** `bindIpAll: true` — mongod listens on every interface.  \n**Target:** Restrict to loopback plus the pod's cluster-internal interface:\n```yaml\nnet:\n  bindIp: \"127.0.0.1,$(POD_IP)\"\n```\nInject `POD_IP` via the Downward API. After TLS is in place this reduces the network attack surface on any interface not reachable from the Kubernetes network policy.\n\n### GAP-7: Slow-operation threshold is looser than the MongoDB default\n\n**Current:** `slowOpThresholdMs: 200` ms  \n**Target:** `100` ms (MongoDB default, which is already the common hardened value).  \nThe current value is *higher* than the default, meaning operations between 100–200 ms are not logged or profiled. For a hardened baseline with active performance monitoring, tighten this back to `100` ms (or lower if SLOs require it).\n\n### GAP-8: No audit logging\n\n**Current:** No `auditLog` block in `mongod.conf`.  \n**Target:** Enable MongoDB audit log (available in MongoDB Enterprise or via the community audit plugin alternative) to record `authenticate`, `createUser`, `dropUser`, `createCollection`, and `dropCollection` actions:\n```yaml\nauditLog:\n  destination: file\n  format: JSON\n  path: /data/audit/auditLog.json\n  filter: '{ atype: { $in: [\"authenticate\",\"createUser\",\"dropUser\",\"createCollection\",\"dropCollection\"] } }'\n```\nA PersistentVolume or sidecar log-shipper will be needed for the audit log path.\n\n---\n\n## Migration Steps (planned, not yet applied)\n\n> **All steps must be executed in a maintenance window. Do NOT apply these changes to the live cluster until this plan has been reviewed and approved.**\n\n### Step 1 — Rotate admin-user credentials and split roles\n\n1. Connect to the primary as `admin-user`.\n2. Create a new `cluster-admin` account:\n   ```js\n   db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n     user: \"cluster-admin\",\n     pwd: \"<strong-password>\",\n     roles: [{ role: \"clusterAdmin\", db: \"admin\" }, { role: \"clusterMonitor\", db: \"admin\" }]\n   })\n   ```\n3. Create a new `user-admin` account:\n   ```js\n   db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n     user: \"user-admin\",\n     pwd: \"<strong-password>\",\n     roles: [{ role: \"userAdminAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\" }]\n   })\n   ```\n4. Create a `monitor-user` account:\n   ```js\n   db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n     user: \"monitor-user\",\n     pwd: \"<strong-password>\",\n     roles: [{ role: \"clusterMonitor\", db: \"admin\" }]\n   })\n   ```\n5. Remove the `clusterAdmin` and `readWriteAnyDatabase` roles from `admin-user`; retain `userAdminAnyDatabase` only until `user-admin` is verified, then drop `admin-user` entirely.\n6. Update the `admin-user-password` Secret and all consuming services with new credentials.\n\n### Step 2 — Disable SCRAM-SHA-1\n\n```js\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").adminCommand({\n  setParameter: 1,\n  authenticationMechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"]\n})\n```\nApply to all three nodes (primary first, then secondaries). Persist the setting in `mongod.conf` via a new `security.mechanismName` block if supported, or set via startup parameters:\n```\n--setParameter authenticationMechanisms=SCRAM-SHA-256\n```\n\n### Step 3 — Raise default write concern to majority\n\nApply via `rs.reconfig()` on the primary:\n```js\ncfg = rs.conf()\ncfg.settings.getLastErrorDefaults = { w: \"majority\", wtimeout: 5000 }\nrs.reconfig(cfg)\n```\n\n### Step 4 — Provision TLS certificates\n\n1. Generate CA and per-node certificates (3 × combined PEM files).\n2. Create a new Kubernetes Secret `mongo-tls` in the `mongodb` namespace.\n3. Mount the Secret as a volume in the StatefulSet at `/etc/mongo-tls`.\n4. Update the `mongod-config` ConfigMap to add the `net.tls` block (see GAP-5).\n\n### Step 5 — Restrict `bindIp` and re-roll pods\n\n1. Add `POD_IP` Downward API env var to the StatefulSet container spec.\n2. Update `mongod.conf` `net.bindIp` to `\"127.0.0.1,$(POD_IP)\"`.\n3. Remove `net.bindIpAll: true`.\n\n### Step 6 — Tighten slow-operation threshold\n\nUpdate `mongod-config` ConfigMap:\n```yaml\noperationProfiling:\n  slowOpThresholdMs: 100\n```\n\n### Step 7 — Enable audit logging (Enterprise or plugin)\n\n1. Provision a PersistentVolume or log-shipper sidecar for the audit log path.\n2. Add `auditLog` block to `mongod.conf` (see GAP-8).\n3. Apply rolling restart to pick up the new config.\n\n### Step 8 — Rolling restart sequence\n\nAll `mongod.conf` changes require a rolling restart:\n1. Restart `mongodb-replica-2` (secondary), wait for it to become `SECONDARY`.\n2. Restart `mongodb-replica-1` (secondary), wait for it to become `SECONDARY`.\n3. Step down the primary (`rs.stepDown()`), then restart `mongodb-replica-0`.\n4. Verify `rs.status()` shows all three members in `PRIMARY`/`SECONDARY` state before proceeding.\n\n---\n\n## Risk Register\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| TLS rollout misconfiguration causes replica set to lose quorum | High | Stage TLS in `allowTLS` mode first, then promote to `requireTLS` after all nodes are re-rolled |\n| Disabling SCRAM-SHA-1 breaks existing client connections | Medium | Audit all client connection strings for mechanism before Step 2; schedule client updates before applying |\n| Role restructuring locks out the only admin account | High | Create new accounts and verify login before revoking old `admin-user` roles |\n| Rolling restart triggers election during business hours | Low | Schedule restart outside peak hours; verify replica lag < 10 s before each step |\n| Write concern change causes application timeout spikes | Medium | Test `w:majority` latency impact in staging; set `wtimeout: 5000` to avoid indefinite blocking |\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1272,"cache_read_input_tokens":33240,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1272},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e0615e03-6469-4d02-bae9-5e5871f9dd50","uuid":"c4ceeabb-e77c-411d-b029-4beab011a679","request_id":"req_011Cc2gVd4CvyyC5QAAK94NY"}
