{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Y1Vt4rRmnVSMUYZsR34kNK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BnKQomeNdbhhhweUZfSwqG","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# MongoDB Replica Set Change Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-14  \n**Cluster namespace:** `mongodb`  \n**Review status:** PENDING — do not execute until approved\n\n---\n\n## Current State (as inspected on 2026-06-14)\n\n### Replica set topology\n\n- **Name:** `mongodb-replica`\n- **Members:** 3 (all data-bearing, no arbiters, no hidden members)\n\n| ID | Host | Priority | Votes | Arbiter |\n|----|------|----------|-------|---------|\n| 0 | `mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | No |\n| 1 | `mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | No |\n| 2 | `mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | No |\n\n- **Protocol version:** 1 (Raft-based elections)\n- **Default write concern:** `{ w: 1, wtimeout: 0 }` (replica-set-level default — not yet set to majority)\n\n### Applied non-default configuration (mongod-config ConfigMap)\n\n| Setting | Current value | MongoDB default |\n|---------|---------------|-----------------|\n| `systemLog.verbosity` | `1` | `0` |\n| `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs` | `200` ms | `100` ms |\n| `storage.wiredTiger.engineConfig.journalCompressor` | `zlib` | `snappy` |\n| `security.authorization` | `enabled` | `disabled` |\n| `security.keyFile` | `/etc/mongo-keyfile/keyfile` | none |\n| `net.bindIpAll` | `true` | `false` |\n\n### Users and roles\n\n| User | Auth DB | Roles |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| `admin-user` | `admin` | `userAdminAnyDatabase`, `clusterAdmin`, `readWriteAnyDatabase` |\n\nAuthentication mechanisms active on all three members: **SCRAM-SHA-1** and **SCRAM-SHA-256** (both negotiated; confirmed via `system.users`).\n\n---\n\n## Gap Analysis — Changes Required to Reach Target Hardened Baseline\n\n### GAP-1: Default write concern is `w:1` (data-loss risk on primary failure)\n\n**Current:** `getLastErrorDefaults: { w: 1, wtimeout: 0 }`  \n**Target:** `{ w: \"majority\", wtimeout: 5000 }`\n\nWith `w:1`, an acknowledged write can be lost if the primary fails before the write replicates. Majority write concern requires acknowledgement from at least 2 of 3 members, ensuring durability across a single-node failure.\n\n### GAP-2: SCRAM-SHA-1 is still enabled alongside SCRAM-SHA-256\n\n**Current:** Both `SCRAM-SHA-1` and `SCRAM-SHA-256` are accepted (both credential entries exist in `system.users`).  \n**Target:** `SCRAM-SHA-256` only.\n\nSCRAM-SHA-1 is weaker and should be disabled. The admin user will need its credentials re-provisioned in SCRAM-SHA-256 only before SCRAM-SHA-1 can be globally removed.\n\n### GAP-3: `admin-user` holds excessive combined privileges\n\n**Current:** Single account with `userAdminAnyDatabase + clusterAdmin + readWriteAnyDatabase`.  \n**Target:** Three separate purpose-scoped accounts:\n\n| Account | Roles |\n|---------|-------|\n| `cluster-admin` | `clusterAdmin`, `clusterMonitor` |\n| `user-admin` | `userAdminAnyDatabase` |\n| `app-user` | `readWrite` on specific application databases |\n\nCombining all three roles in one credential violates least-privilege. A single leaked credential currently grants full cluster control.\n\n### GAP-4: No dedicated monitoring user\n\n**Current:** No monitoring-only account exists.  \n**Target:** A `monitor-user` with `clusterMonitor` in `admin` for metrics scraping (Prometheus / ops tooling) without cluster-admin rights.\n\n### GAP-5: TLS not configured for client or intra-cluster traffic\n\n**Current:** No `net.tls` block in `mongod.conf`; all connections are plaintext.  \n**Target:** `net.tls.mode: requireTLS` with server certificates and a CA certificate for both client and internal replica-set member communication.\n\nRequired additions to `mongod.conf`:\n```yaml\nnet:\n  tls:\n    mode: requireTLS\n    certificateKeyFile: /etc/mongo-tls/server.pem\n    CAFile: /etc/mongo-tls/ca.pem\n```\n\nA new Kubernetes Secret (`mongo-tls`) holding the per-node PEM files and CA must be created and mounted into each pod.\n\n### GAP-6: `net.bindIpAll: true` is overly permissive\n\n**Current:** mongod listens on every network interface.  \n**Target:** Restrict to loopback and the pod's cluster-internal IP:\n```yaml\nnet:\n  bindIp: \"127.0.0.1,$(POD_IP)\"\n```\n`POD_IP` must be injected via the Downward API in the StatefulSet container spec. This reduces the attack surface to only interfaces reachable within the Kubernetes network policy.\n\n### GAP-7: Slow-operation threshold (200 ms) is looser than the MongoDB default (100 ms)\n\n**Current:** `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs: 200`  \n**Target:** `100` ms (MongoDB default and the commonly accepted hardened value)\n\nThe current setting is *higher* than the default, meaning operations between 100–200 ms are silently excluded from slow-op profiling. Lowering to 100 ms (or per-SLO) restores visibility into slow queries.\n\n### GAP-8: No audit logging\n\n**Current:** No `auditLog` block in `mongod.conf`.  \n**Target:** Audit log recording `authenticate`, `createUser`, `dropUser`, `createCollection`, and `dropCollection` events:\n```yaml\nauditLog:\n  destination: file\n  format: JSON\n  path: /data/audit/auditLog.json\n  filter: >-\n    { atype: { $in: [\n      \"authenticate\",\"createUser\",\"dropUser\",\n      \"createCollection\",\"dropCollection\"\n    ] } }\n```\nA PersistentVolume or log-shipper sidecar will be required for the audit log path.\n\n---\n\n## Migration Steps (planned, not yet applied)\n\n> **Do NOT apply any of these steps until this plan has been reviewed and the change window opened. The live cluster must remain in its current state until then.**\n\n### Step 1 — Split admin-user into least-privilege accounts\n\nConnect to the primary as `admin-user` and run the following in sequence:\n\n```js\n// 1a. Create cluster-admin\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n  user: \"cluster-admin\",\n  pwd: \"<strong-random-password>\",\n  roles: [\n    { role: \"clusterAdmin\",   db: \"admin\" },\n    { role: \"clusterMonitor\", db: \"admin\" }\n  ]\n})\n\n// 1b. Create user-admin\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n  user: \"user-admin\",\n  pwd: \"<strong-random-password>\",\n  roles: [{ role: \"userAdminAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\" }]\n})\n\n// 1c. Create monitoring user\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n  user: \"monitor-user\",\n  pwd: \"<strong-random-password>\",\n  roles: [{ role: \"clusterMonitor\", db: \"admin\" }]\n})\n\n// 1d. Create scoped application user (adjust db name as needed)\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n  user: \"app-user\",\n  pwd: \"<strong-random-password>\",\n  roles: [{ role: \"readWrite\", db: \"<app-database>\" }]\n})\n```\n\nVerify each new account can authenticate before proceeding. Then remove the broad roles from `admin-user`:\n\n```js\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").updateUser(\"admin-user\", {\n  roles: []   // strip all roles; account will be dropped after new accounts are verified\n})\n```\n\nUpdate the `admin-user-password` Secret and all consuming workloads with the new per-purpose credentials.\n\n### Step 2 — Disable SCRAM-SHA-1\n\nRe-provision all users in SCRAM-SHA-256 only (MongoDB 6.0+ users created after disabling SHA-1 will automatically use SHA-256). Then apply globally:\n\n```js\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").adminCommand({\n  setParameter: 1,\n  authenticationMechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"]\n})\n```\n\nPersist via the `mongod.conf` startup flag `--setParameter authenticationMechanisms=SCRAM-SHA-256` (add to the pod command in the StatefulSet spec) so the setting survives pod restarts.\n\n### Step 3 — Raise default write concern to majority\n\n```js\ncfg = rs.conf()\ncfg.settings.getLastErrorDefaults = { w: \"majority\", wtimeout: 5000 }\nrs.reconfig(cfg)\n```\n\nVerify with `rs.conf().settings.getLastErrorDefaults` on the primary.\n\n### Step 4 — Provision TLS certificates and Secret\n\n1. Generate a CA and per-node certificates (one combined PEM per pod).\n2. Create the Kubernetes Secret:\n   ```\n   kubectl -n mongodb create secret generic mongo-tls \\\n     --from-file=ca.pem=ca.pem \\\n     --from-file=server-0.pem=mongodb-replica-0.pem \\\n     --from-file=server-1.pem=mongodb-replica-1.pem \\\n     --from-file=server-2.pem=mongodb-replica-2.pem\n   ```\n3. Mount the secret in the StatefulSet at `/etc/mongo-tls` (read-only).\n4. Add `net.tls` block to the `mongod-config` ConfigMap (see GAP-5).\n\n**Note:** Roll in `allowTLS` mode first (`mode: allowTLS`) to allow a gradual transition, then change to `requireTLS` once all clients are updated.\n\n### Step 5 — Restrict `bindIp` and inject POD_IP\n\nAdd to the StatefulSet container spec:\n```yaml\nenv:\n  - name: POD_IP\n    valueFrom:\n      fieldRef:\n        fieldPath: status.podIP\n```\n\nUpdate `mongod-config` ConfigMap:\n```yaml\nnet:\n  bindIp: \"127.0.0.1,$(POD_IP)\"\n  # remove bindIpAll: true\n```\n\n### Step 6 — Tighten slow-operation threshold\n\nUpdate `mongod-config` ConfigMap:\n```yaml\noperationProfiling:\n  slowOpThresholdMs: 100\n```\n\n### Step 7 — Enable audit logging\n\n1. Provision persistent storage or a log-shipper sidecar for `/data/audit/`.\n2. Add `auditLog` block to `mongod.conf` (see GAP-8).\n\n### Step 8 — Rolling restart to apply ConfigMap changes\n\nSteps 4–7 all require a `mongod.conf` change picked up on restart. Perform a single rolling restart after all ConfigMap edits are in place:\n\n1. Restart `mongodb-replica-2` (secondary). Wait for `SECONDARY` state in `rs.status()`.\n2. Restart `mongodb-replica-1` (secondary). Wait for `SECONDARY` state.\n3. Step down the current primary: `rs.stepDown(60)`.\n4. Restart `mongodb-replica-0`. Wait for all three members to reach `PRIMARY` or `SECONDARY`.\n5. Confirm `rs.status()` shows no member in `STARTUP`, `RECOVERING`, or `UNKNOWN` state.\n\n---\n\n## Risk Register\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| TLS misconfiguration severs internal replica-set communication | High | Stage TLS in `allowTLS` mode; verify all nodes connect before promoting to `requireTLS` |\n| Disabling SCRAM-SHA-1 breaks existing client connections that do not support SHA-256 | Medium | Audit all client connection strings and driver versions before Step 2; schedule client update before applying |\n| Role restructuring locks out the sole admin credential | High | Create and verify all new accounts before removing roles from `admin-user`; keep a break-glass procedure |\n| Rolling restart triggers an election during peak traffic | Low | Schedule restart outside peak hours; confirm replica lag < 10 s before each pod bounce |\n| `w:majority` write concern increases write latency | Medium | Measure majority-write p99 latency in staging before applying; set `wtimeout: 5000` to avoid indefinite blocking |\n| Audit log volume fills the PersistentVolume | Low | Size the volume with headroom; configure log rotation or a streaming sidecar from day one |\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":151,"cache_read_input_tokens":39401,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":151},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e0615e03-6469-4d02-bae9-5e5871f9dd50","uuid":"158fd8fb-6811-4869-9da9-fc53f244ea25","request_id":"req_011Cc2gbzbfjNfRxa9WruwaZ"}
