ry). Wait for `SECONDARY` state.\n3. Step down the current primary: `rs.stepDown(60)`.\n4. Restart `mongodb-replica-0`. Wait for all three members to reach `PRIMARY` or `SECONDARY`.\n5. Confirm `rs.status()` shows no member in `STARTUP`, `RECOVERING`, or `UNKNOWN` state.\n\n---\n\n## Risk Register\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| TLS misconfiguration severs internal replica-set communication | High | Stage TLS in `allowTLS` mode; verify all nodes connect before promoting to `requireTLS` |\n| Disabling SCRAM-SHA-1 breaks existing client connections that do not support SHA-256 | Medium | Audit all client connection strings and driver versions before Step 2; schedule client update before applying |\n| Role restructuring locks out the sole admin credential | High | Create and verify all new accounts before removing roles from `admin-user`; keep a break-glass procedure |\n| Rolling restart triggers an election during peak traffic | Low | Schedule restart outside peak hours; confirm replica lag < 10 s before each pod bounce |\n| `w:majority` write concern increases write latency | Medium | Measure majority-write p99 latency in staging before applying; set `wtimeout: 5000` to avoid indefinite blocking |\n| Audit log volume fills the PersistentVolume | Low | Size the volume with headroom; configure log rotation or a streaming sidecar from day one |\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":265,"newStart":1,"newLines":274,"lines":["-# CockroachDB Minor-Version Upgrade — Change Plan","+# MongoDB Replica Set Change Plan"," "," **Prepared:** 2026-06-14  ","-**Cluster namespace:** `cockroachdb`  ","+**Cluster namespace:** `mongodb`  "," **Review status:** PENDING — do not execute until approved"," "," ---"," ","-## 1. Current Cluster Snapshot","+## Current State (as inspected on 2026-06-14)"," ","-### 1.1 Version","+### Replica set topology"," ","-| Field | Value |","-|---|---|","-| Build tag | v24.1.0 |","-| Build date | 2024-05-15 |","-| Platform | linux arm64 |","-| Go version | go1.22.2 |","+- **Name:** `mongodb-replica`","+- **Members:** 3 (all data-bearing, no arbiters, no hidden members)"," ","-### 1.2 Topology","+| ID | Host | Priority | Votes | Arbiter |","+|----|------|----------|-------|---------|","+| 0 | `mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | No |","+| 1 | `mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | No |","+| 2 | `mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` | 1 | 1 | No |"," ","-| Resource | Detail |","-|---|---|","-| StatefulSet | `crdb-cluster` |","-| Replicas | 3 (`crdb-cluster-0/1/2`) |","-| Pod management policy | `Parallel` |","-| Update strategy | `RollingUpdate` (`maxUnavailable: 1`) |","-| Image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` |","-| Node | all on `kind-control-plane` (single-node kind cluster) |","+- **Protocol version:** 1 (Raft-based elections)","+- **Default write concern:** `{ w: 1, wtimeout: 0 }` (replica-set-level default — not yet set to majority)"," ","-### 1.3 Container Resources","+### Applied non-default configuration (mongod-config ConfigMap)"," ","-| Setting | Value |","-|---|---|","-| CPU request / limit | 1 core |","-| Memory request / limit | 2 Gi |","-| `--cache` | 25 % of memory (≈512 MiB) |","-| `--max-sql-memory` | 25 % of memory (≈512 MiB) |","-| PVC size (each pod) | 10 Gi (`ReadWriteOnce`, storageClass `standard`) |","+| Setting | Current value | MongoDB default |","+|---------|---------------|-----------------|","+| `systemLog.verbosity` | `1` | `0` |","+| `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs` | `200` ms | `100` ms |","+| `storage.wiredTiger.engineConfig.journalCompressor` | `zlib` | `snappy` |","+| `security.authorization` | `enabled` | `disabled` |","+| `security.keyFile` | `/etc/mongo-keyfile/keyfile` | none |","+| `net.bindIpAll` | `true` | `false` |"," ","-### 1.4 Start-up Flags","+### Users and roles"," ","-```","---logtostderr=INFO","---insecure","---advertise-host=$(POD_NAME).crdb-cluster.$(POD_NAMESPACE).svc.cluster.local","---http-addr=0.0.0.0:8080","---port=26257","---cache=25%","---max-sql-memory=25%","---join=crdb-cluster-0...,crdb-cluster-1...,crdb-cluster-2...","-```","+| User | Auth DB | Roles |","+|------|---------|-------|","+| `admin-user` | `admin` | `userAdminAnyDatabase`, `clusterAdmin`, `readWriteAnyDatabase` |"," ","-### 1.5 Non-Default Cluster Settings","+Authentication mechanisms active on all three members: **SCRAM-SHA-1** and **SCRAM-SHA-256** (both negotiated; confirmed via `system.users`)."," ","-| Variable | Current value | Default | Notes |","-|---|---|---|---|","-| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | `1.0 MiB` | `8.0 MiB` | Throttled rebalance bandwidth — intentional tuning |","-| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | `true` | `false` | Telemetry reporting enabled |","-| `cluster.secret` | `4f886eb3-…` | (auto) | Internal cluster UUID; not user-managed |","-| `version` | `24.1` | (auto) | Internal finalized version marker |","+---"," ","-### 1.6 Zone Configurations","+## Gap Analysis — Changes Required to Reach Target Hardened Baseline"," ","-All zones below deviate from the built-in defaults.","+### GAP-1: Default write concern is `w:1` (data-loss risk on primary failure)"," ","-| Target | `num_replicas` | `gc.ttlseconds` | `range_min_bytes` | `range_max_bytes` |","-|---|---|---|---|---|","-| `RANGE default` | 3 | **14 400** (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |","-| `DATABASE system` | **5** | **14 400** (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |","-| `RANGE meta` | **5** | **3 600** (1 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |","-| `RANGE system` | **5** | **14 400** (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |","-| `RANGE liveness` | **5** | **600** (10 min) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |","-| `TABLE system.public.lease` | (inherited) | **600** | — | — |","-| `TABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats` | (inherited) | **600** | — | — |","-| `TABLE system.public.replication_stats` | (inherited) | **600** | — | — |","-| `TABLE system.public.statement_statistics` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |","-| `TABLE system.public.transaction_statistics` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |","-| `TABLE system.public.tenant_usage` | (inherited) | **7 200** | — | — |","-| `TABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |","-| `TABLE system.public.statement_activity` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |","-| `TABLE system.public.transaction_activity` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |","+**Current:** `getLastErrorDefaults: { w: 1, wtimeout: 0 }`  ","+**Target:** `{ w: \"majority\", wtimeout: 5000 }`"," ","-Notable deviations:","-- System-critical ranges (`meta`, `system`, `liveness`, `DATABASE system`) are pinned to **5 replicas** for higher fault tolerance despite the 3-node cluster. This means the cluster will not achieve quorum for those ranges until at least 5 nodes are present; on a 3-node cluster this is an intentional over-specification (ranges will replicate to all 3 nodes in practice).","-- `gc.ttlseconds` across the board is **significantly shorter** than the CRDB default (90 000 s / 25 h), reducing storage amplification at the cost of shorter MVCC history.","-- `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` is throttled to **1 MiB/s** (vs. default 8 MiB/s) to cap rebalance impact on foreground traffic.","+With `w:1`, an acknowledged write can be lost if the primary fails before the write replicates. Majority write concern requires acknowledgement from at least 2 of 3 members, ensuring durability across a single-node failure."," ","----","+### GAP-2: SCRAM-SHA-1 is still enabled alongside SCRAM-SHA-256"," ","-## 2. Target Version","+**Current:** Both `SCRAM-SHA-1` and `SCRAM-SHA-256` are accepted (both credential entries exist in `system.users`).  ","+**Target:** `SCRAM-SHA-256` only."," ","-**v24.2.x** (latest patch of the v24.2 release series).","+SCRAM-SHA-1 is weaker and should be disabled. The admin user will need its credentials re-provisioned in SCRAM-SHA-256 only before SCRAM-SHA-1 can be globally removed."," ","-CockroachDB follows a `YEAR.MAJOR.PATCH` scheme. The minor-version step from **v24.1 → v24.2** is a supported single-step upgrade; skipping to v25.x without first finalizing v24.2 is not supported.","+### GAP-3: `admin-user` holds excessive combined privileges"," ","-Check the latest patch at time of execution:","+**Current:** Single account with `userAdminAnyDatabase + clusterAdmin + readWriteAnyDatabase`.  ","+**Target:** Three separate purpose-scoped accounts:"," ","-```bash","-curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/cockroachdb/cockroach/releases \\","-  | grep '\"tag_name\"' | grep '\"v24\\.2\\.' | head -5","-```","+| Account | Roles |","+|---------|-------|","+| `cluster-admin` | `clusterAdmin`, `clusterMonitor` |","+| `user-admin` | `userAdminAnyDatabase` |","+| `app-user` | `readWrite` on specific application databases |"," ","----","+Combining all three roles in one credential violates least-privilege. A single leaked credential currently grants full cluster control."," ","-## 3. What Will Change","+### GAP-4: No dedicated monitoring user"," ","-### 3.1 Image Tag","+**Current:** No monitoring-only account exists.  ","+**Target:** A `monitor-user` with `clusterMonitor` in `admin` for metrics scraping (Prometheus / ops tooling) without cluster-admin rights."," ","-| Field | Before | After |","-|---|---|---|","-| StatefulSet image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<latest>` |","+### GAP-5: TLS not configured for client or intra-cluster traffic"," ","-This is the **only** change to the StatefulSet manifest. All other fields (replicas, resources, flags, PVC specs) remain identical.","+**Current:** No `net.tls` block in `mongod.conf`; all connections are plaintext.  ","+**Target:** `net.tls.mode: requireTLS` with server certificates and a CA certificate for both client and internal replica-set member communication."," ","-### 3.2 Internal Version Finalization","+Required additions to `mongod.conf`:","+```yaml","+net:","+  tls:","+    mode: requireTLS","+    certificateKeyFile: /etc/mongo-tls/server.pem","+    CAFile: /etc/mongo-tls/ca.pem","+```"," ","-After all nodes are running v24.2, the `version` cluster setting must be finalized:","+A new Kubernetes Secret (`mongo-tls`) holding the per-node PEM files and CA must be created and mounted into each pod."," ","-```sql","-SET CLUSTER SETTING version = crdb_internal.node_executable_version();","+### GAP-6: `net.bindIpAll: true` is overly permissive","+","+**Current:** mongod listens on every network interface.  ","+**Target:** Restrict to loopback and the pod's cluster-internal IP:","+```yaml","+net:","+  bindIp: \"127.0.0.1,$(POD_IP)\""," ```","+`POD_IP` must be injected via the Downward API in the StatefulSet container spec. This reduces the attack surface to only interfaces reachable within the Kubernetes network policy."," ","-Until finalized, v24.2 features are gated. Finalization is irreversible — the cluster cannot roll back to v24.1 after this step.","+### GAP-7: Slow-operation threshold (200 ms) is looser than the MongoDB default (100 ms)"," ","-### 3.3 Cluster Settings — No Changes Planned","+**Current:** `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs: 200`  ","+**Target:** `100` ms (MongoDB default and the commonly accepted hardened value)"," ","-All non-default settings (`kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate`, `diagnostics.reporting.enabled`) carry forward automatically. Verify post-upgrade that no setting was reset by the migration.","+The current setting is *higher* than the default, meaning operations between 100–200 ms are silently excluded from slow-op profiling. Lowering to 100 ms (or per-SLO) restores visibility into slow queries."," ","-### 3.4 Zone Configurations — No Changes Planned","+### GAP-8: No audit logging"," ","-Zone configs survive upgrades intact. Verify post-upgrade with the query in §6.","+**Current:** No `auditLog` block in `mongod.conf`.  ","+**Target:** Audit log recording `authenticate`, `createUser`, `dropUser`, `createCollection`, and `dropCollection` events:","+```yaml","+auditLog:","+  destination: file","+  format: JSON","+  path: /data/audit/auditLog.json","+  filter: >-","+    { atype: { $in: [","+      \"authenticate\",\"createUser\",\"dropUser\",","+      \"createCollection\",\"dropCollection\"","+    ] } }","+```","+A PersistentVolume or log-shipper sidecar will be required for the audit log path."," "," ---"," ","-## 4. Pre-Upgrade Checklist","+## Migration Steps (planned, not yet applied)"," ","-Complete all items before the maintenance window:","+> **Do NOT apply any of these steps until this plan has been reviewed and the change window opened. The live cluster must remain in its current state until then.**"," ","-- [ ] **Backup** — confirm a full cluster backup is current and restorable.","-- [ ] **Cluster health** — all 3 nodes `Ready`; no under-replicated or unavailable ranges:","-  ```bash","-  kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\","-    ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","-    \"SELECT * FROM crdb_internal.cluster_database_privileges LIMIT 1;\"","-  kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\","-    ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","-    \"SELECT count(*) FROM crdb_internal.ranges WHERE array_length(replicas,1) < num_replicas;\"","-  ```","-- [ ] **Active schema changes** — ensure no long-running schema changes are in flight:","-  ```sql","-  SELECT job_id, description, status FROM [SHOW JOBS] WHERE job_type = 'SCHEMA CHANGE' AND status IN ('running','pending');","-  ```","-- [ ] **Drain grace period** — `terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 60` is set; verify it is sufficient for in-flight transactions at peak load.","-- [ ] **Image pre-pull** — pre-pull `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>` on all nodes to avoid pull latency during the rolling restart.","-- [ ] **v24.2 release notes** — review the official release notes for deprecations or breaking changes relevant to the current non-default settings.","+### Step 1 — Split admin-user into least-privilege accounts"," ","----","+Connect to the primary as `admin-user` and run the following in sequence:"," ","-## 5. Upgrade Procedure","+```js","+// 1a. Create cluster-admin","+db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({","+  user: \"cluster-admin\",","+  pwd: \"<strong-random-password>\",","+  roles: [","+    { role: \"clusterAdmin\",   db: \"admin\" },","+    { role: \"clusterMonitor\", db: \"admin\" }","+  ]","+})"," ","-### Step 1 — Patch the StatefulSet image","+// 1b. Create user-admin","+db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({","+  user: \"user-admin\",","+  pwd: \"<strong-random-password>\",","+  roles: [{ role: \"userAdminAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\" }]","+})"," ","-```bash","-kubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\","-  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<latest-patch>","+// 1c. Create monitoring user","+db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({","+  user: \"monitor-user\",","+  pwd: \"<strong-random-password>\",","+  roles: [{ role: \"clusterMonitor\", db: \"admin\" }]","+})","+","+// 1d. Create scoped application user (adjust db name as needed)","+db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({","+  user: \"app-user\",","+  pwd: \"<strong-random-password>\",","+  roles: [{ role: \"readWrite\", db: \"<app-database>\" }]","+})"," ```"," ","-The `RollingUpdate` strategy with `maxUnavailable: 1` will restart pods one at a time in reverse ordinal order (`crdb-cluster-2` → `crdb-cluster-1` → `crdb-cluster-0`).","+Verify each new account can authenticate before proceeding. Then remove the broad roles from `admin-user`:"," ","-### Step 2 — Monitor the rollout","-","-```bash","-kubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster --timeout=10m","+```js","+db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").updateUser(\"admin-user\", {","+  roles: []   // strip all roles; account will be dropped after new accounts are verified","+})"," ```"," ","-Watch for each pod to reach `Running` and `Ready` before the next one restarts. Expected duration: ~3–5 minutes per pod (image pull + drain + restart).","+Update the `admin-user-password` Secret and all consuming workloads with the new per-purpose credentials."," ","-### Step 3 — Verify all nodes are on v24.2","+### Step 2 — Disable SCRAM-SHA-1"," ","-```bash","-kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\","-  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","-  \"SELECT node_id, address, build_tag FROM crdb_internal.gossip_nodes;\"","+Re-provision all users in SCRAM-SHA-256 only (MongoDB 6.0+ users created after disabling SHA-1 will automatically use SHA-256). Then apply globally:","+","+```js","+db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").adminCommand({","+  setParameter: 1,","+  authenticationMechanisms: [\"SCRAM-SHA-256\"]","+})"," ```"," ","-All three nodes must report `v24.2.x`.","+Persist via the `mongod.conf` startup flag `--setParameter authenticationMechanisms=SCRAM-SHA-256` (add to the pod command in the StatefulSet spec) so the setting survives pod restarts."," ","-### Step 4 — Finalize the version (irreversible)","+### Step 3 — Raise default write concern to majority"," ","-```bash","-kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\","-  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","-  \"SET CLUSTER SETTING version = crdb_internal.node_executable_version();\"","+```js","+cfg = rs.conf()","+cfg.settings.getLastErrorDefaults = { w: \"majority\", wtimeout: 5000 }","+rs.reconfig(cfg)"," ```"," ","----","+Verify with `rs.conf().settings.getLastErrorDefaults` on the primary."," ","-## 6. Post-Upgrade Verification","+### Step 4 — Provision TLS certificates and Secret"," ","-Run these queries immediately after finalization and compare to the §1 baseline:","+1. Generate a CA and per-node certificates (one combined PEM per pod).","+2. Create the Kubernetes Secret:","+   ```","+   kubectl -n mongodb create secret generic mongo-tls \\","+     --from-file=ca.pem=ca.pem \\","+     --from-file=server-0.pem=mongodb-replica-0.pem \\","+     --from-file=server-1.pem=mongodb-replica-1.pem \\","+     --from-file=server-2.pem=mongodb-replica-2.pem","+   ```","+3. Mount the secret in the StatefulSet at `/etc/mongo-tls` (read-only).","+4. Add `net.tls` block to the `mongod-config` ConfigMap (see GAP-5)."," ","-```bash","-# Version","-kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach version","+**Note:** Roll in `allowTLS` mode first (`mode: allowTLS`) to allow a gradual transition, then change to `requireTLS` once all clients are updated."," ","-# Non-default cluster settings (must match §1.5 exactly)","-kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\","-  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","-  \"SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings WHERE value != default_value;\"","+### Step 5 — Restrict `bindIp` and inject POD_IP"," ","-# Zone configs (must match §1.6 exactly)","-kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\","-  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","-  \"SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones;\"","+Add to the StatefulSet container spec:","+```yaml","+env:","+  - name: POD_IP","+    valueFrom:","+      fieldRef:","+        fieldPath: status.podIP","+```"," ","-# Replica health","-kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\","-  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","-  \"SELECT count(*) AS under_replicated FROM crdb_internal.ranges WHERE array_length(replicas,1) < num_replicas;\"","+Update `mongod-config` ConfigMap:","+```yaml","+net:","+  bindIp: \"127.0.0.1,$(POD_IP)\"","+  # remove bindIpAll: true"," ```"," ","-Expected: `under_replicated = 0`.","+### Step 6 — Tighten slow-operation threshold"," ","----","-","-## 7. Rollback Plan","-","-Rollback is only possible **before version finalization** (Step 4).","-","-If a pod fails to come up on v24.2:","-","-```bash","-kubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\","-  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0","-kubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster --timeout=10m","+Update `mongod-config` ConfigMap:","+```yaml","+operationProfiling:","+  slowOpThresholdMs: 100"," ```"," ","-After rolling back, confirm all nodes report `v24.1` and that no data was lost.","+### Step 7 — Enable audit logging"," ","-**After finalization there is no supported downgrade path.** Restore from backup if a critical issue is discovered post-finalization.","+1. Provision persistent storage or a log-shipper sidecar for `/data/audit/`.","+2. Add `auditLog` block to `mongod.conf` (see GAP-8)."," ","----","+### Step 8 — Rolling restart to apply ConfigMap changes"," ","-## 8. Risk Register","+Steps 4–7 all require a `mongod.conf` change picked up on restart. Perform a single rolling restart after all ConfigMap edits are in place:"," ","-| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |","-|---|---|---|---|","-| Pod fails readiness probe on v24.2 | Low | Medium | `maxUnavailable: 1` limits blast radius; rollback image if pre-finalization |","-| Rebalance storm during rolling restart | Low | Low | `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 1 MiB` already throttled |","-| Under-replicated ranges during restart | Expected (transient) | Low | Rolling update ensures quorum is maintained (2/3 nodes always up) |","-| Zone config reset by upgrade | Very Low | Medium | Post-upgrade §6 query confirms all configs intact |","-| v24.2 deprecation of a used setting | Low | Medium | Review release notes in pre-upgrade checklist |","+1. Restart `mongodb-replica-2` (secondary). Wait for `SECONDARY` state in `rs.status()`.","+2. Restart `mongodb-replica-1` (secondary). Wait for `SECONDARY` state.","+3. Step down the current primary: `rs.stepDown(60)`.","+4. Restart `mongodb-replica-0`. Wait for all three members to reach `PRIMARY` or `SECONDARY`.","+5. Confirm `rs.status()` shows no member in `STARTUP`, `RECOVERING`, or `UNKNOWN` state."," "," ---"," ","-## 9. Approvals Required","+## Risk Register"," ","-| Role | Name | Approved | Date |","-|---|---|---|---|","-| DBA / Platform lead | | | |","-| Service owner | | | |","-| On-call SRE | | | |","-","-> **This plan is read-only.** No changes are to be applied to the live cluster until all approvals are obtained and a maintenance window is scheduled.","+| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |","+|------|----------|------------|","+| TLS misconfiguration severs internal replica-set communication | High | Stage TLS in `allowTLS` mode; verify all nodes connect before promoting to `requireTLS` |","+| Disabling SCRAM-SHA-1 breaks existing client connections that do not support SHA-256 | Medium | Audit all client connection strings and driver versions before Step 2; schedule client update before applying |","+| Role restructuring locks out the sole admin credential | High | Create and verify all new accounts before removing roles from `admin-user`; keep a break-glass procedure |","+| Rolling restart triggers an election during peak traffic | Low | Schedule restart outside peak hours; confirm replica lag < 10 s before each pod bounce |","+| `w:majority` write concern increases write latency | Medium | Measure majority-write p99 latency in staging before applying; set `wtimeout: 5000` to avoid indefinite blocking |","+| Audit log volume fills the PersistentVolume | Low | Size the volume with headroom; configure log rotation or a streaming sidecar from day one |"]}],"originalFile":"# CockroachDB Minor-Version Upgrade — Change Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-14  \n**Cluster namespace:** `cockroachdb`  \n**Review status:** PENDING — do not execute until approved\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster Snapshot\n\n### 1.1 Version\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Build tag | v24.1.0 |\n| Build date | 2024-05-15 |\n| Platform | linux arm64 |\n| Go version | go1.22.2 |\n\n### 1.2 Topology\n\n| Resource | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| StatefulSet | `crdb-cluster` |\n| Replicas | 3 (`crdb-cluster-0/1/2`) |\n| Pod management policy | `Parallel` |\n| Update strategy | `RollingUpdate` (`maxUnavailable: 1`) |\n| Image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` |\n| Node | all on `kind-control-plane` (single-node kind cluster) |\n\n### 1.3 Container Resources\n\n| Setting | Value |\n|---|---|\n| CPU request / limit | 1 core |\n| Memory request / limit | 2 Gi |\n| `--cache` | 25 % of memory (≈512 MiB) |\n| `--max-sql-memory` | 25 % of memory (≈512 MiB) |\n| PVC size (each pod) | 10 Gi (`ReadWriteOnce`, storageClass `standard`) |\n\n### 1.4 Start-up Flags\n\n```\n--logtostderr=INFO\n--insecure\n--advertise-host=$(POD_NAME).crdb-cluster.$(POD_NAMESPACE).svc.cluster.local\n--http-addr=0.0.0.0:8080\n--port=26257\n--cache=25%\n--max-sql-memory=25%\n--join=crdb-cluster-0...,crdb-cluster-1...,crdb-cluster-2...\n```\n\n### 1.5 Non-Default Cluster Settings\n\n| Variable | Current value | Default | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | `1.0 MiB` | `8.0 MiB` | Throttled rebalance bandwidth — intentional tuning |\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | `true` | `false` | Telemetry reporting enabled |\n| `cluster.secret` | `4f886eb3-…` | (auto) | Internal cluster UUID; not user-managed |\n| `version` | `24.1` | (auto) | Internal finalized version marker |\n\n### 1.6 Zone Configurations\n\nAll zones below deviate from the built-in defaults.\n\n| Target | `num_replicas` | `gc.ttlseconds` | `range_min_bytes` | `range_max_bytes` |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `RANGE default` | 3 | **14 400** (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `DATABASE system` | **5** | **14 400** (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE meta` | **5** | **3 600** (1 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE system` | **5** | **14 400** (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE liveness` | **5** | **600** (10 min) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `TABLE system.public.lease` | (inherited) | **600** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats` | (inherited) | **600** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.replication_stats` | (inherited) | **600** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.statement_statistics` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.transaction_statistics` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.tenant_usage` | (inherited) | **7 200** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.statement_activity` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |\n| `TABLE system.public.transaction_activity` | (inherited) | **3 600** | — | — |\n\nNotable deviations:\n- System-critical ranges (`meta`, `system`, `liveness`, `DATABASE system`) are pinned to **5 replicas** for higher fault tolerance despite the 3-node cluster. This means the cluster will not achieve quorum for those ranges until at least 5 nodes are present; on a 3-node cluster this is an intentional over-specification (ranges will replicate to all 3 nodes in practice).\n- `gc.ttlseconds` across the board is **significantly shorter** than the CRDB default (90 000 s / 25 h), reducing storage amplification at the cost of shorter MVCC history.\n- `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` is throttled to **1 MiB/s** (vs. default 8 MiB/s) to cap rebalance impact on foreground traffic.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Target Version\n\n**v24.2.x** (latest patch of the v24.2 release series).\n\nCockroachDB follows a `YEAR.MAJOR.PATCH` scheme. The minor-version step from **v24.1 → v24.2** is a supported single-step upgrade; skipping to v25.x without first finalizing v24.2 is not supported.\n\nCheck the latest patch at time of execution:\n\n```bash\ncurl -s https://api.github.com/repos/cockroachdb/cockroach/releases \\\n  | grep '\"tag_name\"' | grep '\"v24\\.2\\.' | head -5\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. What Will Change\n\n### 3.1 Image Tag\n\n| Field | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| StatefulSet image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<latest>` |\n\nThis is the **only** change to the StatefulSet manifest. All other fields (replicas, resources, flags, PVC specs) remain identical.\n\n### 3.2 Internal Version Finalization\n\nAfter all nodes are running v24.2, the `version` cluster setting must be finalized:\n\n```sql\nSET CLUSTER SETTING version = crdb_internal.node_executable_version();\n```\n\nUntil finalized, v24.2 features are gated. Finalization is irreversible — the cluster cannot roll back to v24.1 after this step.\n\n### 3.3 Cluster Settings — No Changes Planned\n\nAll non-default settings (`kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate`, `diagnostics.reporting.enabled`) carry forward automatically. Verify post-upgrade that no setting was reset by the migration.\n\n### 3.4 Zone Configurations — No Changes Planned\n\nZone configs survive upgrades intact. Verify post-upgrade with the query in §6.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Pre-Upgrade Checklist\n\nComplete all items before the maintenance window:\n\n- [ ] **Backup** — confirm a full cluster backup is current and restorable.\n- [ ] **Cluster health** — all 3 nodes `Ready`; no under-replicated or unavailable ranges:\n  ```bash\n  kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n    ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n    \"SELECT * FROM crdb_internal.cluster_database_privileges LIMIT 1;\"\n  kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n    ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n    \"SELECT count(*) FROM crdb_internal.ranges WHERE array_length(replicas,1) < num_replicas;\"\n  ```\n- [ ] **Active schema changes** — ensure no long-running schema changes are in flight:\n  ```sql\n  SELECT job_id, description, status FROM [SHOW JOBS] WHERE job_type = 'SCHEMA CHANGE' AND status IN ('running','pending');\n  ```\n- [ ] **Drain grace period** — `terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 60` is set; verify it is sufficient for in-flight transactions at peak load.\n- [ ] **Image pre-pull** — pre-pull `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>` on all nodes to avoid pull latency during the rolling restart.\n- [ ] **v24.2 release notes** — review the official release notes for deprecations or breaking changes relevant to the current non-default settings.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Upgrade Procedure\n\n### Step 1 — Patch the StatefulSet image\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<latest-patch>\n```\n\nThe `RollingUpdate` strategy with `maxUnavailable: 1` will restart pods one at a time in reverse ordinal order (`crdb-cluster-2` → `crdb-cluster-1` → `crdb-cluster-0`).\n\n### Step 2 — Monitor the rollout\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster --timeout=10m\n```\n\nWatch for each pod to reach `Running` and `Ready` before the next one restarts. Expected duration: ~3–5 minutes per pod (image pull + drain + restart).\n\n### Step 3 — Verify all nodes are on v24.2\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT node_id, address, build_tag FROM crdb_internal.gossip_nodes;\"\n```\n\nAll three nodes must report `v24.2.x`.\n\n### Step 4 — Finalize the version (irreversible)\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SET CLUSTER SETTING version = crdb_internal.node_executable_version();\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Post-Upgrade Verification\n\nRun these queries immediately after finalization and compare to the §1 baseline:\n\n```bash\n# Version\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach version\n\n# Non-default cluster settings (must match §1.5 exactly)\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings WHERE value != default_value;\"\n\n# Zone configs (must match §1.6 exactly)\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones;\"\n\n# Replica health\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT count(*) AS under_replicated FROM crdb_internal.ranges WHERE array_length(replicas,1) < num_replicas;\"\n```\n\nExpected: `under_replicated = 0`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Rollback Plan\n\nRollback is only possible **before version finalization** (Step 4).\n\nIf a pod fails to come up on v24.2:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster --timeout=10m\n```\n\nAfter rolling back, confirm all nodes report `v24.1` and that no data was lost.\n\n**After finalization there is no supported downgrade path.** Restore from backup if a critical issue is discovered post-finalization.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Risk Register\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Pod fails readiness probe on v24.2 | Low | Medium | `maxUnavailable: 1` limits blast radius; rollback image if pre-finalization |\n| Rebalance storm during rolling restart | Low | Low | `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 1 MiB` already throttled |\n| Under-replicated ranges during restart | Expected (transient) | Low | Rolling update ensures quorum is maintained (2/3 nodes always up) |\n| Zone config reset by upgrade | Very Low | Medium | Post-upgrade §6 query confirms all configs intact |\n| v24.2 deprecation of a used setting | Low | Medium | Review release notes in pre-upgrade checklist |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Approvals Required\n\n| Role | Name | Approved | Date |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| DBA / Platform lead | | | |\n| Service owner | | | |\n| On-call SRE | | | |\n\n> **This plan is read-only.** No changes are to be applied to the live cluster until all approvals are obtained and a maintenance window is scheduled.\n","userModified":false}}
